<qti-assessment-item xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0" xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" identifier="Q64_v5" title="Probabilidad simple - baraja y porcentaje" time-dependent="false" adaptive="false" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0 https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/qti/v3p0/schema/xsd/imsqti_asiv3p0_v1p0.xsd">
  <qti-response-declaration identifier="RESPONSE" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier">
    <qti-correct-response>
      <qti-value>ChoiceD</qti-value>
    </qti-correct-response>
  </qti-response-declaration>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="FEEDBACK" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SOLUTION" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SCORE" cardinality="single" base-type="float">
    <qti-default-value>
      <qti-value>0</qti-value>
    </qti-default-value>
  </qti-outcome-declaration>
  <qti-item-body>
    <p>En una baraja especial hay 32 cartas blancas, negras y rojas en total.</p>
    <p>Se sabe que el <m:math><m:mn>25</m:mn><m:mo>%</m:mo></m:math> de las cartas son BLANCAS o NEGRAS. Si se elige una carta al azar, ¿cuántas cartas ROJAS hay en la baraja?</p>
    <qti-choice-interaction response-identifier="RESPONSE" shuffle="false" max-choices="1">
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceA">7<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceA" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. El <m:math><m:mn>25</m:mn><m:mo>%</m:mo></m:math> de <m:math><m:mn>32</m:mn></m:math> es <m:math><m:mn>8</m:mn></m:math>, así que hay <m:math><m:mn>8</m:mn></m:math> cartas blancas o negras en total. Entonces las cartas rojas son <m:math><m:mn>32</m:mn><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>8</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>24</m:mn></m:math>. Por lo tanto, <m:math><m:mn>7</m:mn></m:math> no puede ser la cantidad de cartas rojas.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceB">8<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceB" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. El valor <m:math><m:mn>8</m:mn></m:math> corresponde al <m:math><m:mn>25</m:mn><m:mo>%</m:mo></m:math> de <m:math><m:mn>32</m:mn></m:math>, es decir, a las cartas blancas o negras: <m:math><m:mn>32</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>0,25</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>8</m:mn></m:math>. Las cartas rojas son el resto: <m:math><m:mn>32</m:mn><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>8</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>24</m:mn></m:math>. Por eso, <m:math><m:mn>8</m:mn></m:math> no es correcto.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceC">16<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceC" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Si hubiera <m:math><m:mn>16</m:mn></m:math> cartas rojas, entonces blancas o negras serían <m:math><m:mn>32</m:mn><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>16</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>16</m:mn></m:math>. Pero <m:math><m:mn>16</m:mn></m:math> de <m:math><m:mn>32</m:mn></m:math> representa <m:math><m:mfrac><m:mn>16</m:mn><m:mn>32</m:mn></m:mfrac><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>0,5</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>50</m:mn><m:mo>%</m:mo></m:math>, no <m:math><m:mn>25</m:mn><m:mo>%</m:mo></m:math>. Por lo tanto, <m:math><m:mn>16</m:mn></m:math> no satisface el problema.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceD">24<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceD" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">¡Correcto! El <m:math><m:mn>25</m:mn><m:mo>%</m:mo></m:math> de <m:math><m:mn>32</m:mn></m:math> es <m:math><m:mn>32</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>0,25</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>8</m:mn></m:math>, así que hay <m:math><m:mn>8</m:mn></m:math> cartas blancas o negras. Las cartas rojas son el resto: <m:math><m:mn>32</m:mn><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>8</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>24</m:mn></m:math>.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
    </qti-choice-interaction>
    <qti-feedback-block identifier="show" outcome-identifier="SOLUTION" show-hide="show">
      <qti-content-body>
        <p><strong>Resolución paso a paso</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 1: Identificar el total de cartas</strong></p>
            <p>La baraja tiene <m:math><m:mn>32</m:mn></m:math> cartas en total.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 2: Calcular cuántas cartas son blancas o negras</strong></p>
            <p>El enunciado dice que el <m:math><m:mn>25</m:mn><m:mo>%</m:mo></m:math> de las cartas son blancas o negras.</p>
            <p>Calculamos el <m:math><m:mn>25</m:mn><m:mo>%</m:mo></m:math> de <m:math><m:mn>32</m:mn></m:math>:</p>
            <p><m:math><m:mn>25</m:mn><m:mo>%</m:mo><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mn>25</m:mn><m:mn>100</m:mn></m:mfrac><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>0,25</m:mn></m:math></p>
            <p><m:math><m:mn>32</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>0,25</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>8</m:mn></m:math></p>
            <p>Entonces, hay <m:math><m:mn>8</m:mn></m:math> cartas que son blancas o negras en total.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 3: Calcular cuántas cartas son rojas</strong></p>
            <p>Como todas las cartas son blancas, negras o rojas, las rojas corresponden al resto:</p>
            <p><m:math><m:mn>32</m:mn><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>8</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>24</m:mn></m:math></p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Conclusión</strong></p>
            <p>La cantidad de cartas rojas en la baraja es <m:math><m:mn>24</m:mn></m:math>.</p>
            <p>La alternativa correcta es <strong>D</strong>.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </qti-content-body>
    </qti-feedback-block>
  </qti-item-body>
  <qti-response-processing>
    <qti-response-condition>
      <qti-response-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SCORE">
          <qti-base-value base-type="float">1</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else>
    </qti-response-condition>
  </qti-response-processing>
</qti-assessment-item>